Media assets

Still images, data visualizations, charts, infographics

All images must be saved into the ../assets/img/ folder and its subfolders. The Cloud Storage Use in Europe visualization of our dataset published in the Slovak PCR report can be found ../assets/img/6x4/ind_cloud_storage_files@en.png in English version, and ../assets/img/6x4/ind_cloud_storage_files@sk.png in Slovak.

knitr::include_graphics(file.path("assets", "img", "6x4", "ind_cloud_storage_files@en.png"))

  • Whenever visualizations are named in several languages, create one visualizatio publication with files denoting the language versions with @en, @bg, etc.
  • For maximum reusability, it is a good idea to save programatically created charts in several aspect ratios: 16x9 and 6x4, and maybe even in square, and often with title captions and without.
  • Every visualization must have a single, globally unique identifier, in this case DOI:10.6084/m9.figshare.20455224.This way both humans and computers can find our asset.
knitr::include_graphics(file.path("assets", "img", "6x4", "ind_cloud_storage_files@sk.png"))

Every image will be published on Zenodo or Figshare. These particular files can be found on https://figshare.com/articles/figure/Cloud_Storage_Use_in_Europe/20455224. We also have a bibliographic reference file, in this case ../bib/data/ind_cloud_storage_files.bib for correctly citing our visualization.

FigShare and Zenodo make sure that other reseaerchers of this topic will find our work, and if they reuse the visualization, they give proper attribution to it. This file, although published in a non-public report, has 4-5 downloads per months because it can be found.

Video files

Moving images should be placed in ../assets/video/.

Text

Bibliographic references

There are many bibliography management software in the market. We use Zenodo because it is free to use, open-source, and compatible with many paid bibliography management tools.

Our Zotero libraries should be synchronized to the GitHub repositories. The bibliographic reference files must be saved in: - [x] ../bib/ for books, published articles, manuscripts, complex documents that may contain themselves data, references to other text, and images. - [x] ../bib/data for datasets. - [x] ../bib/img for images. - [x] ../bib/img for videos.

## Contents of the ../bib/data/ind_cloud_storage_files.bib  file:
